# Git commit messages — nest-auth-example

Always use **Conventional Commits** format:

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

[optional body — explain WHY, not what]

[optional Co-Authored-By footer]
```

## Types

| Type | When |
|------|------|
| `feat` | New feature or page (FCM row lands) |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change with no behavior change |
| `test` | Adding or fixing tests |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `chore` | Tooling, scripts, config |
| `ci` | CI/CD pipeline changes |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |

## Scopes for this project

| Scope | Area |
|-------|------|
| `api` | `apps/api` backend (NestJS) |
| `web` | `apps/web` frontend (Next.js) |
| `auth` | Auth wiring, guards, decorators, library integration |
| `dashboard` | `apps/web/app/dashboard/**` |
| `platform` | Platform admin area |
| `prisma` | Schema, migrations, seed |
| `infra` | Docker, Redis, config modules |
| `ws` | WebSocket gateway or client |
| `account` | `apps/api/src/account/` |
| `invitations` | `apps/api/src/invitations/` |
| `users` | `apps/api/src/users/` |
| `deps` | Dependency updates |

## Rules

- Subject line ≤ 72 characters, imperative mood ("add", "fix", not "added", "fixes")
- Body explains the **why**, not the what — the diff shows the what
- Reference Feature Coverage Matrix rows when a feature lands: `Covers FCM #8, #10.`
- Never include `.env`, secrets, `node_modules`, `dist`, `coverage`, `.next`
- Never commit `console.log`, `@ts-ignore`, or `// eslint-disable` left in source
- Add `Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>` when AI assisted

## Examples

```
feat(dashboard): add MFA setup flow with QR code and recovery codes modal

Covers FCM rows #8 (TOTP enrollment) and #10 (recovery codes).
QR rendered client-side via qrcode pkg — no external service contacted.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
```

```
feat(api): add custom InvitationsModule with Redis+Prisma dual-write

Library's InvitationService is not exported; replicate the Redis key
format (nest-auth-example:inv:{sha256(token)}) so the library's accept
endpoint can still consume the stored token.
```

```
fix(api): scope invitation list query by tenantId

listByTenant() was missing the tenantId filter, exposing cross-tenant
invitation data on GET /api/invitations.
```
